this is a typescript project we are going to create ... 

js doesnt have any type error...
ts has type error  ... 

TypeScript enforces type safety, so passing incorrect types (e.g., true instead of a number) causes a compile-time error.
JavaScript allows any type, leading to unexpected behavior at runtime like true + "OK" resulting in "trueOK".


Usecase :- 
<!-- javascript hasnot type error .... -->
function sum(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}
// Example usage
console.log(sum(5, 10)); // Output: 15
console.log(sum("4", true)); // Output: 4true  //no type error


<!-- typescript : has type error ...  -->
function sum(a: number, b: number): number {
  return a + b;
}
// Example usage
console.log(sum(5, 10)); // Output: 15
console.log(sum(5,true)) //type error 







npx tsc is used for converting tscode(index.js) to jscode(index.js) which is executable in node Environment 










